ezdb
Interface RangeTable<H,R,V>

Type Parameters:
H - The type of the hash key for this key/value table.
R - The type of the range key for this key/value table.
V - The type of the value for this key/value table.
All Superinterfaces:
Table<H,V>
All Known Implementing Classes:
EzLevelDbTable, TreeMapTable
public interface RangeTable<H,R,V>
extends Table<H,V>

A hash/range table that supports bucketing rows together by hash key, and doing range queries within the buckets. Rows are uniquely identified by combining their hash key and range key.

Author:
criccomini

put

void put(H hashKey,
         R rangeKey,
         V value)
Put a value into the table, keyed by both the hash and range key. If a row already exists for the hash/range pair, it should be overwritten.

Parameters:
hashKey - A key used group rows together.
rangeKey - A secondary key used to sort rows within the same hash key group.
value - The value to be persisted.

range

TableIterator<H,R,V> range(H hashKey,
                           R fromRangeKey)
Get all rows with a given hash key, and a range key that's greater than or equal to the "from" range key provided.

Parameters:
hashKey - A key used group rows together.
fromRangeKey - The range key to use as the starting point. If an exact match doesn't exist for this hash/range pair, the nearest range key that is larger than this range key will be used as the starting point.
Returns:
An iterator of all remaining TableRows in this hash key group, ordered by their range key.

range

TableIterator<H,R,V> range(H hashKey,
                           R fromRangeKey,
                           R toRangeKey)
Get all rows with a given hash key, and a range key that's greater than or equal to the "from" range key, and less than or equal to the "to" range key. That is, the "from" range key is inclusive, and the "to" range key is exclusive.

Parameters:
hashKey - A key used group rows together.
fromRangeKey - The range key to use as the starting point. If an exact match doesn't exist for this hash/range pair, the nearest range key that is larger than this range key will be used as the starting point.
toRangeKey - The range key to use as the end point (exclusive). If an exact match doesn't exist, the nearest range key that is less than this range key will be used as the end point (inclusive).
Returns:
An iterator of all remaining TableRows in this hash key group that have a range key [fromRangeKey, toRangeKey).

delete

void delete(H hashKey,
            R rangeKey)
Delete a value for a given hash/range pair. If no value exists for a given hash/range pair, this should be a no op.

Parameters:
hashKey - A key used group rows together.
rangeKey - A secondary key used to sort rows within the same hash key group.
